cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing (NLP) tasks such as disambiguation of medical term abbreviations in clinical notes. The use of a neural topic-attention model also suggests a focus on NLP techniques. 

It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as the proposed few-shot learning approach involves training a neural model on limited labeled data. 

cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is another possible sub-category as the paper deals with disambiguation of ambiguous medical terms, which is a common problem in information retrieval systems. 

cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also a possibility as the paper proposes a novel approach to address a challenging problem in NLP using machine learning techniques. 

Finally, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a potential sub-category as the paper uses a neural model to improve sentence representations for disambiguation.
